text: The 2005 NCAA Division I Men's Swimming and Diving Championships were contested in March 2005 at the University Aquatic Center at the University of Minnesota in Minneapolis, Minnesota at the 82nd annual NCAA-sanctioned swim meet to determine the team and individual national champions of Division I men's collegiate swimming and diving in the United States. Auburn again topped the team standings, finishing 77 points ahead of Stanford.
